The need for careful planning and deliberation of actions, the desire to complete what has been started, the difficulties of switching from one type of activity to another; accuracy, correctness, pedantry, patience in work and social interaction; at the same time, the motivation of avoiding failure dominates the motivation of high achievements; in general, a serious attitude to life combined with the difficulty of free self-realization

Currently, the problems associated with free self-realization are not relevant for the individual; behavior has a rather spontaneous, relaxed nature, there is no pronounced tendency to increased reflection and critical introspection, careful deliberation and planning of actions; a moderate degree of responsibility, commitment, and plasticity is characteristic (lack of a pronounced tendency to fix experiences, an accepted line of behavior, completion of what has been started)

The absence of problems associated with free self-realization, increased control of behavior and emotional reactions, fixed forms of behavior and experiences; in activities and social relationships – naturalness, ease, lack of inclination to careful planning, deliberation and completion of what has been started, ease of switching from one type of activity and contacts to another, impatience, mobility; motivation of high achievements prevails over the motivation of avoiding failure.

Spontaneity of emotional reactions, looseness of behavior, free self-realization, dynamism of decisions, assessments, actions, lack of introspection and tendency to reflection, self-confidence; easy attitude to problems, failures, responsibility, lack of fear of new activities, contacts, focus on success and high achievements

The high value of the assessment reflects the high probability of unrestrained, poorly controlled and predictable behavior; the predominance of affective forms of reaction (mainly extrapunitive orientation), irritability, quick temper; non-conformity and rashness of actions; poor tolerance of stress with the possibility of maladaptive forms of behavior, aggressiveness; at the same time, there are features of hypersensitivity to injustice, sensitivity and affective rigidity

The increased value of the assessment reflects increased emotional excitability, weakening of the ability to willfully control emotions, unstable, unbalanced behavior in interpersonal interaction, the possibility of irritable and angry reactions in frustrating situations, increased sensitivity with a tendency to "accumulate" negative experiences (insufficient plasticity of emotions); reduced tolerance to stress and, in general, the regulatory capabilities of the psyche

The evaluation value falls into the zone of an uncertain diagnosis. This means that currently there are no significant problems associated with the control of affective reactions; behavior is characterized by sufficient poise, balance (the predominance of extrapunitive reactions is not expressed); one can assume the ability to suppress sensitivity, irritability and other negatively colored emotional reactions and states, a moderate (sufficient) level of tolerance to stress, the ability to use constructive mechanisms of psychological overcoming (coping behavior); in general, the absence of significant difficulties in regulating behavior and social adaptation

The lowered value of the assessment reflects a balanced, stable and predictable pattern of behavior, the adequacy of emotional response methods, good intellectual and volitional control of behavior; there is no pronounced tendency to form "stuck" sensitive reactions (plasticity of emotions); stability in stress, constructive forms of psychological overcoming and adaptation

The low value of the assessment reflects emotional stability and balance, the absence of affective conditioning and rashness of behavior, as well as affective rigidity and sensitivity; high frustration tolerance, the predominance of plastic and constructive ways to overcome stress

The high value of the assessment reflects significant social distancing, immersion in the world of one\'s own experiences, the need for solitude, experiencing discomfort in situations of broad social interaction, an individual pattern of behavior, ways of activity and solving problem situations

The increased value of the assessment reflects social distancing, preference for activities that do not involve broad social interaction, autonomy of behavior (independence from the assessments of others), independence of judgments, the desire to suppress external manifestations of emotions; trusting relationships can develop with a very limited circle of people

The evaluation value falls into the zone of uncertain diagnosis. This means that at present there is a moderate level of social activity, sociability and conformity, the absence of significant difficulties in implementing social contacts, a moderate need for understanding and support from others, the possibility of trusting relationships with a relatively wide range of people and the natural manifestation of emotions in behavior

The lowered value of the assessment reflects rather sociable, open behavior, willingness to cooperate, orientation to the opinions of others, the need for their help and support, open expression of emotions outside and the ability to establish trusting relationships with a fairly wide range of people; plasticity and lack of difficulties in implementing social contacts, establishing new connections
A low score value reflects a distinct socially oriented behavior, openness and ease in contacts, the need for communication, a good ability for group interaction

The high value of the assessment reflects excessive concentration on individual mental and somatic functions, on the state of one\'s health as a whole, the desire to maintain an exclusively correct lifestyle in order to avoid illness, anxiety concerns about the risk of developing the disease

The increased value of the assessment reflects concentration on the state of one\'s health, attentive attitude to minor manifestations of malaise, increased control over behavior and lifestyle in order to avoid situations potentially associated with the risk of disease (hypothermia, overexertion, etc.), search for information about various diseases and compliance with all prescriptions for their prevention; inflexibility of behavior in general, discomfort if necessary, changes in habitual life stereotypes

The evaluation value falls into the zone of an uncertain diagnosis. This means that at present, increased control over the state of one\'s health, individual mental and somatic functions, lifestyle and behavior in connection with the risk of developing diseases is not typical for the subject; there is a moderate degree of plasticity and a reasonable approach to the problem of preserving and maintaining health, to obtaining the necessary information about diseases and measures to prevent them, a balanced nature of experiences related to the state of health in general

The lowered value of the assessment reflects the lack of a tendency to increased control over the state of one\'s health and behavior (lifestyle) that can affect its level, plasticity (lack of fixation on unpleasant sensations, experiences, as well as anxiety in situations requiring changes in behavioral stereotypes), a light (non-anxious) attitude to emerging symptoms of malaise, the possibility of deviation from prescriptions and recommendations for treatment and maintenance of health.
A low score value reflects a careless, non-anxious attitude to one\'s state of health, lack of desire for preventive measures due to the risk of illness and a sparing lifestyle

The high value of the assessment reflects poor adaptability in various social situations, a decrease in social perception and understanding of the nuances of interpersonal relationships, lack of criticality regarding the correctness and acceptance of their behavior by others

The increased value of the assessment reflects a decrease in the level of social adaptability, manifested in insufficient ability to understand the nuances of interpersonal relationships (social perception and empathy), in the inflexibility of social contacts, non-conformity; a reduced level of socialization is also manifested in insufficient experience (dexterity, sophistication) in solving difficult social situations, in insufficient ability to control the clarity and acceptance of one\'s judgments and actions, in the resulting ambivalent attitude towards others (the need for communication is combined with the fear of being awkward, misunderstood); there may be a deviation from generally accepted forms of behavior due to personal unconventionality, unusual attitudes, poor assimilation of social norms

The evaluation value falls into the zone of uncertain diagnosis. This means that there are currently no pronounced signs of violations of social adaptation due to insufficient assimilation of generally accepted norms, a decrease in social perception, empathy, communication skills, flexibility and confidence in the process of interpersonal interaction

The lowered value of the assessment reflects a well-balanced social behavior based on the correct assimilation of generally accepted patterns of behavior, on general good communication skills, a high level of socio- and autoperception in the process of interpersonal interaction, plasticity, compliance and interest in social contacts
The low value of the assessment reflects significant adaptive capabilities of the individual, plasticity, differentiation of social behavior; good communication skills and a desire for cooperation
